hts stand to be gained from the techniques and methods pioneered by countless scholars over the decades in a variety of fields. Muhammad and the Empires of Faith offers both an authoritative introduction to the multilayered traditions surrounding the life of Muhammad and a compelling exploration of how these traditions interacted with the broader landscape of Late Antiquity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aarabic.  abiography.  acaliph.  acloister.  acommerce.  adoctrina iacobi.  aearly islam.  afaith.  ahadith.  ahistory.  aislam.  aislamic history.  akeys to paradise.  alate antiquity.  amerchant.  amonk.  amuhammad.  amuslim.  anonfiction.  apreaching.  aprophet.  areligion.  areligious discourse.  areligious history.  areligious leaders.  ascared texts.  aspirituality.  atrader.  aumayyads.  avision.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020 Englishz978311070483908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020z9783110704631oZDB-23-DGD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520974524zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520974524423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520974524.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Engl